Tickets 5.27.6.1</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2705:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">The latest version of Event Tickets improves PayPal&#8217;s and Square&#8217;s handling of the failure endpoint.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\"> testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Improves PayPal&#8217;s and Square&#8217;s handling of the failure endpoint.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new string added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-5-27-6-1/\">Event Tickets 5.27.6.1</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"The Events Calendar 6.15.20\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-20/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 08 Apr 2026 21:02:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2553147\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:588:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release The latest version of The Events Calendar resolves several 404 errors by improving AJAX pagination for SSR, fixing paginated list view requests on MariaDB, and implementing a URL rewrite fallback for the day view. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing....</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-20/\">The Events Calendar 6.15.20</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3118:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest version of The Events Calendar resolves several 404 errors by improving AJAX pagination for SSR, fixing paginated list view requests on MariaDB, and implementing a URL rewrite fallback for the day view.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Changelog:</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Make SSR respect AJAX pagination so direct page URLs no longer return 404s.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Prevent 404 errors for paginated TEC list view requests on MariaDB.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rewrite the day view URL to query-param form and fall back to the default view when day view is disabled, preventing a 404 after a page refresh. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column2553147_e235af-3f\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>13 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-20/\">The Events Calendar 6.15.20</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"The Events Calendar 6.15.19\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-19/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:55:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2553143\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:615:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release The latest version of The Events Calendar focuses on strengthening security and data integrity by tightening capability checks for Venues, Organizers, categories, and Event Aggregator imports. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixes Bugs squashed in this release: ⚙️...</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-19/\">The Events Calendar 6.15.19</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3784:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest version of The Events Calendar focuses on strengthening security and data integrity by tightening capability checks for Venues, Organizers, categories, and Event Aggregator imports. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Ensures Venues and Organizers linked to an event, are still honoring their individual capabilities.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Strengthens capability checks for categories and terms. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tightens capability checks and server-side validation for Event Aggregator scheduled import edits. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Adds filters: `tec_events_views_v2_url_allowed_query_args`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column2553143_c1cf42-18\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p>Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>2 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>20 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-15-19/\">The Events Calendar 6.15.19</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"Event Tickets 5.27.6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-5-27-6/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 07 Apr 2026 16:55:38 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Event Tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"event tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=